begin_memory_text: We became acquainted with each other making small talk about our city and states. We also began discussing the effects of (our) the American country right now.
middle_memory_text: We became more engaged and talked a bit more about New Jersey and a bit deeper into the impact of the Covied-19 virus.
end_memory_text: We also talked about how people are acting negatively by not taking precautions such as wearing masks.
rest_of_day_open: Another day of wondering what will happen to me and the world at large! I am so concerned and just taking it one day at a time. I wish I knew how it would go but I just don't. Regardless, I we will be okay in the long run I just will be hopeful.
critical_positive: We both agreed that these are trying times for everyone. We agreed that kindness and thinking about others is the key to survival basically right now. So that made it work out perfectly! so glad he was on the same page as me. I was nervous that the person wasn't going to be a believer of the virus.
critical_negative: Every thing worked well in my opinion. Honestly it was amazing and made my day! Like we seemed to agree on everything and provided support for each other! is that weird lol We had no issues it was honest open and upfront. Thanks for choosing a good conversationalist. I was concerned.

begin_memory_text: We exchanged backgrounds on each other so we could continue with the conversation based on each of our life experiences.
middle_memory_text: We talked about my proximity to NYC and the Jersey Shore and her lifelong desire to come here and experience the two.
end_memory_text: The division we are experiencing under the leadership of the current administration, and how things have to change.
rest_of_day_open: It's going to be nice out the next couple days after two straight days of rain. I'm fortunate to be able to set my own hours at work for the most part so I'm going to take advantage of the nice weather to the fullest extent possible. I will continue to be nervous about the upcoming elections because there is so much at stake.
critical_positive: She was very easy to speak with so the conversation did not have to be manufactured. At a couple points, I caught myself dominating the conversation so I tried to back off and let her lead. She did exactly that and we continued to have a good natural conversation. It was easy because we both had similar viewpoints on the topics about which we talked.
critical_negative: The video quality was not the best, but I'm just nitpicking. It was not a signifiant negative factor, and there was not much else that I can think of. I did have to take the video chat in my garage because the kids were inside attending remote learning sessions, and it was kind of cold.
